5:
What's this? I thought you knew
better than to show up uninvited,
Rec Register.
9:
You know me—when there's urgent
business to take care of, I can't stay
put.
13:
And what business have you come
for?
18:
Oh, you know. Just that kid you
kidnapped, the relic you stole, and
any other secrets you've been
keeping quiet about.
23:
You drive a hard bargain. Perhaps
you should take your business
elsewhere.
49:
I must admit, I was almost worried
for a moment there. You're from a
different world, aren't you, Regis? I
had to scramble to adjust the
parameters.
59: Why can't I... hear the sprites?
63:
Say hello to the sacred relic you
were looking for—the Anti-Observer.
Those fools at the Academy had no
idea what they were tampering
with...
65:
But I do. Above ground, it can be
used to sever your connection to the
elements... Here in the Kaleidoscope,
however, it can do so much more.
69:
Welcome to my shift. The world you
believed in doesn't exist here.
73:
Why? Because only those with the
ability to rewrite worlds have the
power to act inside this space.
76:
I should mention, Phiria... You count
as one of those people.
81:
I had originally intended to drag the
serpents into the Kaleidoscope, but
instead I was lucky enough to run
into you!
84:
Time for you to serve your purpose,
Oracle!
92:
You were both cultivated in identical
ways. By that same logic, you can
both be utilized the same way...
94:
Relax. Give in. Release your heart to
me, and you need not suffer any
longer...
97:
None of this will be your fault. You
have no choice in the matter, no
burden to bear.
103:
Everything will be fine, child. All you
have to do is obey.
106:
Then you can blame all your woes
on me, if that is what you wish.
